like the generator and Swagger aren't available due to the provided dependencies. I should mention resolved artifacts and dependencies in the summary, but only in JSON format. There's a risk that if the driver imports certain dependencies, those entries might be redundant, and I'll ensure valid JSON in the end.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The Swagger 2 module is an add-on with `jsonschema-generator` and `swagger-annotations` declared as provided dependencies, so meaningful tests need those APIs explicitly on the test classpath.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"com.github.victools:jsonschema-generator:5.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The module is used by registering `Swagger2Module` with `SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder`; the module POM declares `jsonschema-generator` as provided, so the generator API is not supplied transitively by the tested artifact.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"io.swagger.core.v3:swagger-annotations:2.2.41\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Coverage requires model classes annotated with Swagger/OpenAPI `@Schema` and `@ArraySchema`; the module POM declares `swagger-annotations` as provided, and version 2.2.41 is the version managed by the 5.0.0 parent.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For version 5.0.0, use Jackson 3 types from the `tools.jackson` packages when inspecting generated schemas, e.g. `tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode`, not the older `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode`. Build tests around `new Swagger2Module()` registered with `SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder` and annotated sample classes using `io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.media.Schema`/`ArraySchema`. No Docker image, environment variable, or system property setup appears necessary.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Existing 4.38.0 tests import Jackson 2 `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode`; carrying that import forward to 5.0.0 will keep javac failing even with the correct dependencies.\",\n    \"If the generated scaffold already applies the victools BOM and declares these provided dependencies explicitly, these deterministic entries may be redundant; local Gradle compile remains authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c529ce5b0f6f155016a4055f5f8048197b2f0b0849f063801\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1937, "output": 1318, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28855, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782601193849, "responseId": "resp_0c529ce5b0f6f155016a4055ea5c588197a8eebab2b0b91373"}, "toolResults": []}
